premise_source_doc_sentence: Lalo Schifrin  (  born Boris Claudio Schifrin , June 21 , 1932  )  is an Argentine pianist , composer , arranger and conductor .
He is best known for his large body of film and TV scores since the 1950s , including the `` Theme from Mission : Impossible '' and `` Enter the Dragon '' .
He has received four Grammy Awards and six Oscar nominations .
Associated with the jazz music genre , Schifrin is also noted for work with Clint Eastwood in the late 1960s , 1970s and 1980s , particularly the Dirty Harry films .
Lalo Schifrin  (  born Boris Claudio Schifrin , June 21 , 1932  )  is an Argentine pianist , composer , arranger and conductor .
Lalo = Brilliance  (  subtitled The Piano of Lalo Schifrin  )  is an album by Argentine composer , pianist and conductor Lalo Schifrin recorded in 1962 and released on the Roulette label .

The Dissection and Reconstruction of Music From the Past as Performed By the Inmates of Lalo Schifrin 's Demented Ensemble as a Tribute to the Memory of the Marquis De Sade is a 1966 studio album by Lalo Schifrin .
There 's a Whole Lalo Schifrin Goin ' On is an album by Argentine composer , pianist and conductor Lalo Schifrin recorded in 1968 and released on the Dot label .
The album was rereleased in 1968 on the Roulette label as Lalol : The Latin Sound of Lalo Schifrin .
